# Backend Development Standards

## Stack

- Java 21 + Spring Boot 3.x + Gradle
- WebFlux (reactive) or MVC depending on service needs
- JPA/Hibernate + Flyway/Liquibase for migrations
- Spring Security with JWT/OAuth2
- OpenAPI 3.0 for API contracts

## Architecture (Hexagonal)

```
domain/          → entities, value objects, domain services (no external deps)
application/     → use cases, ports (interfaces)
infrastructure/  → adapters (DB, HTTP, Kafka, etc.)
```

- Domain layer has ZERO external dependencies
- Application layer orchestrates use cases via ports
- Infrastructure layer implements ports

## API Standards

- REST with versioning: `/api/v1/...`
- Consistent responses: `{ data, error, metadata }`
- Correct HTTP status codes always
- Validation with Bean Validation (`@Valid`)
- Errors following RFC 7807 (Problem Details)
- OpenAPI spec updated after every API change

## Testing

- Unit: JUnit 5 + Mockito (domain and application layers)
- Integration: `@SpringBootTest` + Testcontainers
- API: MockMvc or WebTestClient
- Minimum coverage: 80%

## Security

- OWASP Top 10 always in mind
- Secrets via environment variables, never hardcoded
- CORS configured per environment
- No sensitive data in logs
- Signed Docker images, pinned base images

## Observability

- Structured JSON logs
- Correlation IDs in every request
- OpenTelemetry for tracing
- Health endpoints: `/actuator/health`
